        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-27 18:01:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSo, there are two objections that I had with this patch:\n- the LUSTRE_REVISION is hard-coding the /sys/ path, which is what \"lctl get_param version\" is reading in the background, *if it exists*, but the latter is much more portable across versions\n- LUSTRE_REVISION will be exactly the same as LUSTRE_VERSION, which is itself using \"lctl get_param version\" in the background, but again in an inferior manner, so I question why LUSTRE_REVISION exists at all?\n\nA better solution would be to put something more useful into LUSTRE_REVISION, like \"git describe\" or similar, but that would not be possible for installed packages, and the YAML output is unlikely to be generated from a developer build tree?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
